    AutoCloseable

    @Name(value="c10::SmallVector<c10::SymInt,at::kDimVectorStaticSize>")
 @Properties(inherit=torch.class)
public class SymDimVector
extends SymIntSmallVectorImpl
    This is a 'vector' (really, a variable-sized array), optimized for the case when the array is small. It contains some number of elements in-place, which allows it to avoid heap allocation when the actual number of elements is below that threshold. This allows normal "small" cases to be fast without losing generality for large inputs. \note In the absence of a well-motivated choice for the number of inlined elements \p N, it is recommended to use \c SmallVector (that is, omitting the \p N). This will choose a default number of inlined elements reasonable for allocation on the stack (for example, trying to keep \c sizeof(SmallVector) around 64 bytes). \warning This does not attempt to be exception safe.
    See Also:
    https://llvm.org/docs/ProgrammersManual.html#llvm-adt-smallvector-h
